# TaskForge Stack Assessment

When performing AWS Well-Architected assessment of the TaskForge stack:

## Scope

- **Read:** `../taskforge-backend`, `../taskforge-security`, and this repo (`taskforge-platform-infra`)
- **Write:** This repo only. Do NOT modify `aws-repo-well-architected-advisor` or the sibling repos (backend, security)

## Outputs (all in this repo)

- **Assessments:** `docs/assessment/` — review reports, findings, scorecard
- **Terraform updates:** `terraform/*.tf` — patches and incremental fixes
- **IAM execution requirements:** `terraform/iam-execution-policy.json` + `docs/iam-execution-requirements.md` — permissions for the role running Terraform (EKS, RDS, VPC, ECR, Secrets Manager, etc.)
- **Compliance mapping:** `docs/compliance-mapping.md` (if created)

## Workflow

1. Read taskforge-backend (app code, configs, CI/CD)
2. Read taskforge-security (security service, configs)
3. Read this repo (Terraform)
4. Infer full architecture and workload profile
5. Produce evidence-based recommendations
6. Write assessment to `docs/assessment/`
7. Apply Terraform patches to `terraform/` as needed

## Reference

Use guidance from `aws-repo-well-architected-advisor` (sibling repo) for Well-Architected pillars, evidence model, and recommendation patterns. Do not edit the advisor repo.
